      "type": "answer",
      "text": "\nNow I have a complete picture. Here's the full audit:\n\n---\n\n## FirstGens Portal — Component Audit\n\n### How the routing / wiring works\n\nThe app has a `useRealApi()` gate in `store.ts`. When running at `/app/*` (production), it fires real `frappe-ui` API calls. When running standalone (prototype), it hits the in-memory mock store.\n\n### View-by-view wiring status\n\n| View | Backend | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Home** (`/`) | `GET GP Discussion` — real endpoint, filtered + paginated | ✅ Real |\n| **Space** (`/spaces/:id`) | `GET GP Discussion` scoped to project | ✅ Real |\n| **Post Detail** (`/posts/:id`) | Read: mock. Write: `POST GP Comment` via `createComment` → real | ⚠️ Partial |\n| **Courses** (`/courses`) | `getCourses()` → mock store | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Course Detail** (`/courses/:id`) | `getCourse()`, `getChaptersForCourse()`, `getLessonsForChapter()` → all mock | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Lesson** (`/courses/.../lessons/:id`) | Progress tracking, YouTube embed — all mock | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Course New** (`/courses/new`) | `createCourse()` → mock store (no real LMS API) | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Members** (`/members`) | `getUsers()` → mock store | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Member Detail** (`/members/:id`) | Recent posts, badges, energy points — all mock | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Messages** (`/messages`) | DM threads → Raven channels (headless, no real API) | ❌ Headless |\n| **Thread** (`/messages/:id`) | Send/read DMs → Raven messages (headless) | ❌ Headless |\n| **Events** (`/events`) | `getEvents()`, `setRSVP()`, `createEvent()` → all mock | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Mentors** (`/mentors`) | `requestMentor()` → real `INSERT FG Mentor Match`. Fetch: mock. | ⚠️ Partial |\n| **Notifications** (`/notifications`) | `getNotifications()` → mock. `markAllNotificationsRead()` → local only. | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Settings** (`/settings`) | `updateProfile()`, `updateUserSettings()` → local only (no real User API) | ❌ Mocked |\n| **Docs** (`/docs`) | Static array, no API | ✅ Correct (static) |\n| **PostCard** | Reactions via `toggleReaction()` → real API call on real; poll, sentiment → mock | ⚠️ Partial |\n| **NewPostModal** | `createDiscussion()` → real `POST GP Discussion` on real backend | ✅ Real (write) |\n| **Similar posts** | `findSimilarPostsAsync()` → calls `fg_companion.api.similar_discussions` → falls back to mock | ⚠️ Falls back |\n\n### The real integration gaps\n\n1. **Courses / LMS** — all reads and writes are mock. `createCourse()` in `store.ts` has no Frappe API call. This is the biggest hole — every course card, enrollment, lesson navigation, progress bar is fake data.\n\n2. **DMs (Raven)** — the code is structured around Raven's DocTypes (`Raven Channel`, `Raven Message`) and the type comments say \"headless\", but there's no `useRealApi()` branch for thread listing or message sending. Raven *is* installed in the bench, so the endpoints exist — just not wired.\n\n3. **Notifications** — reads from a mock `Notification Log`; real production would hit Frappe core's `Notification Log` DocType.\n\n4. **Settings / profile writes** — `updateProfile` writes to the mock store only.\n\n5. **Mentor Match** — requests POST to real `FG Mentor Match` but there's no read (no `getMatchesAsync` hitting the API).\n\n---\n\n### Frappe UI adoption: what's there vs what's custom\n\n**Key finding: `frappe-ui` is in `package.json` but not a single component is imported anywhere in the source.** The CSS comments reference frappe-ui design tokens, but every UI element is hand-rolled.\n\n| Component | Current approach | Frappe UI equivalent | Effort |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `AppLayout` | Fully custom nav, sidebar, badges | `FeatherIcon`, `Dropdown`, badge patterns from `frappe-ui` | Medium |\n| `PostCard` | Custom card with inline reactions | `Card`, `Avatar` from `frappe-ui` | Low-Medium |\n| `NewPostModal` | Custom Teleport modal, toolbar stub | `Dialog`, `TextInput` from `frappe-ui` | Low |\n| `MessagesView` + `ThreadView` | Custom split-pane layout | Closest to Raven's actual UI — keep custom | Medium-High |\n| `CourseDetailView` | Custom chapter/lesson accordion | `Accordion`, `Card` from `frappe-ui` | Low-Medium |\n| `SettingsView` | Custom form with `Toggle` | `FormControl`, `Switch` from `frappe-ui` | Low |\n| `MemberDetailView` | Custom profile header, badges grid | `Avatar`, `Badge` from `frappe-ui` | Low |\n| `AppAvatar` | Letter-avatar with background color | `frappe-ui/Avatar` — already closer to the real thing | Trivial |\n| `SentimentBadge`, `Toggle` | Pure presentational, trivial | — | Not worth it |\n| `PollCard` | Custom poll UI | — | Keep custom |\n| `SidebarItem` | 10-line component | — | Keep custom |\n\n### Rough effort estimate for Frappe UI migration\n\n| Tier | Views | Est. time |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Swap-in** (Dialog, Card, Avatar, Badge, Switch) | PostCard, NewPostModal, Settings, MemberDetail, Forms | 2–4 hrs |\n| **Partial** (adopt patterns + tokens, keep layout) | AppLayout, CourseDetailView, EventsView | 4–6 hrs |\n| **Keep custom** (intentional divergence from Frappe UI) | Messages/Thread, PollCard, Docs | — |\n| **Total** | | **~1–2 days** |\n\n### Verdict\n\nThe app is well-structured — the mock/real split in `store.ts` is clean and ready to flip on. The main unlock is wiring Courses (LMS), DMs (Raven), and Notifications to their real endpoints. The Frappe UI adoption is low-effort since the patterns already align — it's mostly a find-and-replace of custom components with `frappe-ui` equivalents plus adopting the CSS variable naming.\n\nWant me to tackle any of those gaps — starting with wiring Courses to real LMS, or the Frappe UI swap?",
      "timestamp": 1781981753319
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a comprehensive picture of the codebase. Let me compile my findings and present a detailed audit.\n\nHere's what I've found:\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Frontend: Vue 3 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS v4 + frappe-ui (installed but unused) + custom design system\n- Backend: Frappe framework (my-bench)\n- DocTypes: GP (gameplan), LMS (lms), Raven (DMs), HD (helpdesk), FG (custom companion app)\n- Mock layer: In-memory seed data with a `useRealApi()` switch that routes to real Frappe API when in `/app`\n\n\n- Routing is fully wired to real API endpoints in production with Frappe API calls, while the design system uses custom tokens and hardcoded heading styles with no frappe-ui components, though the types do reference Frappe DocTypes for consistency.\n\nNow I'm mapping each route to its underlying DocType: HomeView and SpaceView pull from GP Discussion filtered by project, PostDetailView is a single GP Discussion, CourseDetailView and LessonView tap into LMS, MembersView and MemberDetailView use GP User Profile, MessagesView and ThreadView use Raven, EventsView and NotificationsView are custom, and the remaining views use various GP and custom DocTypes with the store handling the routing.\n\nFor the real API calls, HomeView fetches GP Discussions with ordering and filtering, PostDetailView creates comments in GP Comment, NotificationsView reads from Notification Log, and Tickets create HD Tickets in the system.\n\nDMs in Raven are headless with no real API integration yet, Events are fully mocked with the createEvent function not wired to any endpoint, Courses are entirely mock with createCourse being a stub, and the similar posts feature uses a custom method that currently falls back to mock data.\n\nMentors use a custom DocType with real insertion for requests but no fetch calls, sentiment analysis is mocked, and settings stay in-memory without being persisted.\n\nLooking at the UI components, AppAvatar is fully custom with letter-based avatars and color theming, AppLayout has the full navigation with badges, modals, and sidebar fully wired, PostCard is custom with reactions, sentiment badges, and polls that are all wired, while NewPostModal creates discussions in real but is otherwise fully functional.\n\nThe remaining components are all custom-built: Toggle, SentimentBadge, SidebarItem, and PollCard are custom as well.\n\nFor Frappe UI compatibility, the 10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION doc should guide the refactor, though frappe-ui is installed but not actually used anywhere in the codebase. AppLayout, PostCard, the forms, Settings tab, and MemberDetailView are all highly compatible for migration since they already follow similar patterns.\n\nThe remaining components are more custom with unique aesthetics that would need partial rewrites: CourseDetailView has its own chapter/lesson hierarchy, NewPostModal uses a custom layout and rich text buttons, MessagesView and ThreadView implement a split-panel layout similar to Raven, and PostDetailView is already fairly compatible. AppAvatar and the Sentiment/Toggle badges are too trivial to migrate.\n\nThe real blockers are mock-only data in Events and Courses, the DMs headless setup needing actual Raven channel creation, and the fact that Frappe UI's FormDialog could handle most of the form workflows. The timeline for a full Frappe UI refactor across all components would take considerable effort.",
      "timestamp": 1781981795995
    },
