    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have enough context to plan the full implementation. Let me now plan this properly:\n\n1. **Create DocTypes in `fg_companion`** (Python JSON files + controller)\n2. **Create backend API endpoints** for the new DocTypes\n3. **Seed data script** - Python script to push mock data to DB\n4. **Frontend: wire store to real API** and swap custom components for frappe-ui primitives\n\nLet me start creating everything. This is a big task - let me use a todo list.\n\nLet me start with the DocTypes first.\n\nFor each DocType I need:\n- `.json` file in `doctype/` folder\n\n\n- `.py` controller file\n- optionally `.xml` for permissions\n\nNow I'm mapping out the specific DocTypes I need to create. The Event DocType will track event details like title, description, and timing, along with attendee management and RSVPs. I'll also need a Mentor Match DocType for connecting mentors and mentees with status tracking, plus an AI Settings DocType to store configuration for sentiment analysis and vector search capabilities.\n\nLooking at the existing schema, I see that GP User Profile, GP Team, GP Project, GP Discussion, and GP Comment are already in place through gameplan. I need to fill in the gaps with my new DocTypes and then handle LMS content—LMS Course and LMS Chapter already exist, so I'll need to either seed data into those or create additional supporting DocTypes as needed.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the full migration plan: setting up the custom DocTypes for FG Events, FG Event Attendees, FG Mentor Match, FG AI Settings, and FG User Settings, then creating the backend API endpoints for each, seeding the mock data into the database, and finally updating the frontend store to use real API calls instead of mocks.\n\nThis is a substantial undertaking, so I should approach it methodically. For the DocTypes, I'll need to create the JSON configuration files, Python controller classes, and potentially XML permission files for each one.\n\nCreating DocType files...",
