      "text": "Now let me write all the JSON files for the DocTypes. I'll write them all at once using the edit tool.\n\nFor FG Event:\n- `fg_event.json`: fields for title, description, space (GP Project), event_type (Select), starts_on (Datetime), ends_on (Datetime), location_type (Select), bbb_meeting_id, external_link, physical_address, rsvp_required (Check), capacity (Int), hosted_by (Link User)\n- Permissions: System Manager (all), Website User (read)\n\nFor FG Event Attendee:\n- `fg_event_attendee.json`: fields for event (Link FG Event), user (Link User), rsvp_status (Select: Going, Maybe, Not Going, Attended, No Show)\n\n\n- istable: 1 (it's a child table)\n- No permissions needed (managed by parent)\n\nFor FG Mentor Match:\n- `fg_mentor_match.json`: fields for mentee (Link User), mentor (Link User), status (Select: Requested, Active, Completed, Ended Early), matched_via (Select: Manual, Self-Requested, Algorithmic Suggestion), match_notes (Small Text)\n- Permissions: System Manager (all), Website User (read, create)\n\nFor FG AI Settings:\n- `fg_ai_settings.json`: single doctype, fields for enable_sentiment (Check), sentiment_alert_threshold (\n\nFloat), enable_vector_search (Check)\n- istable: 0 (single doc)\n- Permissions: System Manager (all)\n\nFor FG User Settings:\n- `fg_user_settings.json`: fields for user (Link User, unique), email_on_mention (Check), email_on_reply (Check), email_weekly_digest (Check), push_on_dm (Check), push_on_mention (Check), show_in_member_directory (Check), allow_dm_from_anyone (Check), theme (Select: system, light, dark), language (Select: en, es, fr), timezone (Data)\n- Permissions: System Manager (all), Website User (read, write own)\n\nNow I'm creating the Python controller files for each doctype.",
