      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Wait, the module is already \"FG Companion\" in the JSON. But Frappe is resolving it to `frappe.core.doctype.fg_event`. Let me check if the issue is something else. Looking at the error again:\n\n```\nModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'frappe.core.doctype.fg_event'\n```\n\nThe error is `frappe.core.doctype.fg_event` — this means Frappe is looking in `frappe.core.doctype`. The \"FG Companion\" module should map to `fg_companion.fg_companion`. Let me check how the module mapping works.\n \nActually, I'm realizing the real problem — in Frappe v15, DocType modules follow the pattern `frappe.modules.get_module_name(doctype, module)`, which resolves to something like `fg_companion.fg_companion.doctype.fg_event`. But the error message shows `frappe.core.doctype.fg_event`, which is the fallback path Frappe uses when it can't find the correct module. So the module mapping itself might not be configured correctly for `fg_companion`.\n\nLooking at the DocType JSON, the `module` field is set to `\"FG Companion\"`, which should resolve to the Python module path `fg_companion.fg_companion`. But Frappe might be defaulting to `frappe.core.doctype` if it can't find a matching module for that label — this typically happens when the app uses non-standard module paths or when the `modules.txt` file doesn't properly register the \"FG Companion\" module.\n\nExamining how the gameplan app structures its modules: the module is \"Gameplan\" and it resolves to `gameplan.gameplan.gameplan`, which means the convention is `<app_name>.<app_name>.<module_name>`. So for the fg_companion app, \"FG Companion\" should resolve to `fg_companion.fg_companion.fg_companion` — the path `fg_companion/fg_companion/doctype/` is correct, but I need to verify the module name is properly registered. The DocType was created with the correct JSON, so I need to figure out why the module path isn't resolving properly. Looking at the seed error, it seems `frappe.get_doc()` is trying to find the module in `frappe.core.doctype` instead of where I actually put it, which suggests the module path mapping is broken somewhere.\n\nWait, I think I see the issue now. The seed script creates a new DocType with `frappe.get_doc()` rather than loading an existing one, so the `module` field in the DocType record should match what's in the JSON. But if it's showing `frappe.core.doctype` instead of `FG Companion`, then either the JSON's module field got overwritten during creation, or something else is overriding it.\n\nLooking at the DocType creation process, `frappe.get_doc()` should preserve the module field from the dictionary I'm passing in. Since I'm explicitly setting `\"module\": \"FG Companion\"` in the defaults, that should stick. Let me trace through what's actually happening in the seed script to see where the mismatch is occurring. I need to check what the `module` field is actually set to in the DocType record right now, since the error message shows Frappe is looking for `frappe.core.doctype.fg_event` instead of the expected module path. The traceback confirms the issue is in `load_doctype_module` — it's using the wrong module reference instead of the custom one I specified.\n\nI should just run the migration command to let Frappe automatically fix the DocType module paths, since that's the standard workflow for ensuring they're correct.",
