      "text": "Wait, looking at the seed script output again: `SKIP GP User Profile/sienna@example.com: ('GP User Profile', 'sienna-rae-martinez-1', IntegrityError(1062, \"Duplicate entry 'sienna@example.com' for key 'user'\"))` - the GP User Profile was inserted with a different name (`sienna-rae-martinez-1` auto-generated) because the name field is auto-generated (By script) but the user field is unique. The GP User Profile doctype uses `autoname` of \"By script\" which generates names like `sienna-rae-martinez-1`. But we're trying to insert with `name: sienna@example.com` which conflicts on the `user` unique constraint.\nLooking at the GP User Profile schema, the `name` field uses \"By script\" naming with `user` as the unique field, so when we insert with `name: sienna@example.com` but the script generates `sienna-rae-martinez-1` instead, we end up with a name mismatch and a duplicate key violation on the `user` field since sienna@example.com already exists.\n\nFor the FG Event DocType, I'm tracing through the module resolution - when the doctype JSON specifies `name: \"FG Event\"` and `module: \"FG Companion\"`, Frappe's module loading logic constructs the module path by looking up \"FG Companion\" in the app's modules, which should resolve to `fg_companion.fg_companion.doctype`. The issue is that Frappe might be defaulting to `frappe.core.doctype` instead when it can't find the module. I need to verify that \"FG Companion\" is properly registered in the fg_companion app's modules configuration. me check if the app has a `modules.txt` or if the module name is set in the DocType record itself. Actually, looking at this more carefully — the DocType was created with `module: \"FG Companion\"` in the JSON, but when Frappe creates a DocType record, it might override the module based on the app that called `new_app`. Let me trace through what actually happened: the JSON has `\"module\": \"FG Companion\"`, `bench migrate` creates the table and inserts the DocType record, but the actual module field value depends on which app initiated the creation — and since this came from `bench new-app`, it should have used `fg_companion.fg_companion` as the default module, not `frappe.core`. Looking at the bench framework code, when `new-app` creates a DocType JSON, it sets the module based on the app's module name, and in this case it's using the capitalized app title \"FG Companion\" which maps to `fg_companion.fg_companion`. But the error suggests it's falling back to `frappe.core.doctype` — so I need to figure out where that fallback is coming from. I'm realizing the JSON files I generated don't have the `\"custom\"` field that the gameplan GP Discussion JSON includes, so Frappe might be interpreting them differently. Let me check the DocType record in the database to see what `custom` value was actually set.",
