      "text": "Two issues:\n1. GP User Profile: trying to insert with the email as the `name` field, but gameplan auto-generates the name from the user's full name (sienna-rae-martinez-1). I need to either skip GP User Profiles or handle them differently.\n\n2. GP Discussion: \"Could not find Project: csx\" - the project wasn't created. Let me check why.\n\n3. FG Event: event_type and location_type values don't match what the DocType expects.\n\nLet me investigate each issue:\n- For GP User Profile: the `name` field in gameplan's GP User Profile is auto-generated from the user's full_name, not the email. \n\nThe IntegrityError shows a duplicate key on the email field itself, not the name—so gameplan's GP User Profile likely has a unique constraint on the email field that I'm violating by trying to use the email as the name. For GP Project, the s() function returned None, which means the project creation failed silently, so I need to trace back why that's happening.",
      "timestamp": 1781985580966
