    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "`\"autoname\": \"autoincrement\"` — GP Project ignores my `name` field and auto-generates an integer. So \"csx\" is never found. Let me rewrite the seed to use titles for lookups and store the actual generated names:\n",
      "timestamp": 1781985617908
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I understand. GP Project has `\"naming_rule\": \"Autoincrement\"` and `\"autoname\": \"autoincrement\"`. This means the `name` field is auto-generated as an incrementing integer, NOT the string I passed (like \"csx\"). So when I try to create a project with `name=\"csx\"`, Frappe ignores that and generates a new auto-increment name. But then, the project exists in the DB with an auto-generated name, and when I try to check `frappe.db.exists(\"GP Project\", \"csx\")`, it returns False because the project was created with a different name.\n\nThat's why the projects were created (from the first seed run), but the discussions couldn't find them by the name \"csx\".\n\n\nThe solution is to query for projects by title instead of name, or use a different naming strategy that allows custom identifiers. For discussions, I need to link them to projects by their actual auto-generated names rather than arbitrary string IDs. Let me fix the seed script to handle the autoincrement naming properly.",
      "timestamp": 1781985643508
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"content\": \"#!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"Seed fg_companion + gameplan from prototype mock data.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nimport frappe\\nfrappe.init(site=\\\"mysite.localhost\\\", sites_path=\\\"/home/andiekobbie/my-bench/sites\\\")\\nfrappe.connect()\\n\\ndef s(doctype, name, defaults):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Insert if not exists; return doc. Print skip on dup.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    if frappe.db.exists(doctype, name):\\n        print(f\\\"  exists: {doctype}/{name}\\\")\\n        return frappe.get_doc(doctype, name)\\n    try:\\n        d = frappe.get_doc({\\\"doctype\\\": doctype, **defaults})\\n        if name:\\n            d.name = name\\n        d.insert(ignore_permissions=True)\\n        print(f\\\"  created: {doctype}/{d.name}\\\")\\n        return d\\n    except Exception as e:\\n        print(f\\\"  SKIP {doctype}/{name}: {e}\\\")\\n        return None\\n\\n# \\u2500\\u2500 GP Teams \\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\nprint(\\\"=== Teams ===\\\")\\nteams = {\\n    \\\"general\\\":  s(\\\"GP Team\\\", \\\"general\\\",  {\\\"title\\\": \\\"General\\\",  \\\"is_private\\\": 0}),\\n    \\\"academic\\\": s(\\\"GP Team\\\", \\\"academic\\\", {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Academic\\\", \\\"is_private\\\": 0}),\\n}\\n\\n# \\u2500\\u2500 GP Projects \\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n=== Projects ===\\\")\\n# Use title as unique key (name is autoincrement, can't set it)\\ndef project_by_title(title):\\n    row = frappe.db.get_value(\\\"GP Project\\\", {\\\"title\\\": title}, \\\"name\\\", as_dict=True)\\n    if row:\\n        print(f\\\"  exists: GP Project/{row.name} ('{title}')\\\")\\n        return row.name\\n    d = frappe.get_doc({\\\"doctype\\\": \\\"GP Project\\\", \\\"title\\\": title})\\n    d.insert(ignore_permissions=True)\\n    print(f\\\"  created: GP Project/{d.name} ('{title}')\\\")\\n    return d.name\\n\\npid_csx   = project_by_title(\\\"Computer Science\\\")\\npid_welan = project_by_title(\\\"Welsh Language\\\")\\npid_mh    = project_by_title(\\\"Mental Health\\\")\\npid_fin   = project_by_title(\\\"Student Finances\\\")\\n\\n# \\u2500\\u2500 GP Discussions \\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n=== Discussions ===\\\")\\ndiscs = [\\n    (None, pid_csx,   \\\"sienna@example.com\\\", \\\"A-level CS coursework help\\\",  \\\"Recursion in my NEA is really tricky.\\\"),\\n    (None, pid_csx,   \\\"kwame@example.com\\\",  \\\"CS exam revision tips?\\\",       \\\"6 weeks left, not sure where to start.\\\"),\\n    (None, pid_welan, \\\"priya@example.com\\\",  \\\"Cymraeg Gweithio group\\\",       \\\"Weekly Welsh chat, all levels welcome.\\\"),\\n    (None, pid_mh,    \\\"leila@example.com\\\",  \\\"First week at university\\\",      \\\"Everything feels a bit overwhelming.\\\"),\\n    (None, pid_fin,   \\\"marcus@example.com\\\", \\\"Bursary application dates?\\\",    \\\"Cannot find when they open.\\\"),\\n]\\nfor _did, pid, author, title, content in discs:\\n    title_exists = frappe.db.get_value(\\\"GP Discussion\\\", {\\\"project\\\": pid, \\\"title\\\": title}, \\\"name\\\", as_dict=True)\\n    if title_exists:\\n        print(f\\\"  exists: Discussion '{title}' in project {pid}\\\")\\n        continue\\n    d = frappe.get_doc({\\n        \\\"doctype\\\": \\\"GP Discussion\\\",\\n        \\\"project\\\": pid, \\\"title\\\": title,\\n        \\\"content\\\": f\\\"<p>{content}</p>\\\",\\n        \\\"status\\\": \\\"Open\\\", \\\"author_id\\\": author\\n    })\\n    d.insert(ignore_permissions=True)\\n    print(f\\\"  created: Discussion/{d.name}\\\")\\n\\n# \\u2500\\u2500 FG Events \\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n=== FG Events ===\\\")\\nevents = [\\n    (\\\"Welcome Week Mixer\\\", \\\"Informal meetup for first-years.\\\",  \\\"Networking\\\",              \\\"2026-09-25 18:00:00\\\", \\\"Online (External Link)\\\", \\\"https://meet.example.com\\\", 30),\\n    (\\\"CS Drop-in\\\",         \\\"Weekly CS revision help.\\\",          \\\"Drop-in Office Hours\\\",    \\\"2026-09-30 16:00:00\\\", \\\"Online (BigBlueButton)\\\",  \\\"fg-cs-dropin\\\",               20),\\n]\\nfor title, desc, etype, starts, ltype, link, cap in events:\\n    if frappe.db.exists(\\\"FG Event\\\", {\\\"title\\\": title}):\\n        print(f\\\"  exists: FG Event '{title}'\\\")\\n        continue\\n    try:\\n        doc = frappe.get_doc({\\\"doctype\\\": \\\"FG Event\\\", \\\"title\\\": title})\\n        doc.description = desc\\n        doc.event_type = etype\\n        doc.starts_on = starts\\n        doc.location_type = ltype\\n        doc.capacity = cap\\n        if \\\"BigBlueButton\\\" in ltype:\\n            doc.bbb_meeting_id = link\\n        else:\\n            doc.external_link = link\\n        doc.insert(ignore_permissions=True)\\n        print(f\\\"  created: FG Event/{doc.name}\\\")\\n    except Exception as e:\\n        print(f\\\"  ERROR FG Event '{title}': {e}\\\")\\n\\n# \\u2500\\u2500 FG AI Settings \\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\u2500\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n=== FG AI Settings ===\\\")\\nif not frappe.db.exists(\\\"FG AI Settings\\\", \\\"FG AI Settings\\\"):\\n    try:\\n        d = frappe.get_doc({\\n            \\\"doctype\\\": \\\"FG AI Settings\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"FG AI Settings\\\",\\n            \\\"enable_sentiment\\\": 1, \\\"sentiment_alert_threshold\\\": 0.3,\\n            \\\"enable_vector_search\\\": 1\\n        })\\n        d.insert(ignore_permissions=True)\\n        print(\\\"  created: FG AI Settings\\\")\\n    except Exception as e:\\n        print(f\\\"  ERROR FG AI Settings: {e}\\\")\\nelse:\\n    print(\\\"  exists: FG AI Settings\\\")\\n\\nfrappe.db.commit()\\nprint(\\\"\\\\nSeed complete!\\\")\\n\", \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\seed_fg_companion2.py\"}",
      "output": "Wrote file successfully.\n\n<system-reminder>\nYou just created or modified a file. If this file IS the deliverable the user asked for (document, report, image, spreadsheet, archive, audio, video, code artifact, etc.), you MUST include it in your response with `<media src=\"/absolute/path\" />`; do not only print the path. If it is only an intermediate/source edit, no media tag is needed.\n</system-reminder>",
