    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I understand the store.ts. The key thing is `useRealApi()` returns `true` when `IS_PRODUCTION` is true and there's a CSRF token. `IS_PRODUCTION` is true when the pathname starts with `/app`. So on the portal (at `/portal/`), it uses the mock data.\n\nThe task is to wire the real APIs for:\n1. **Events** (`getEvents`, `getEvent`, `getAttendees`) - uses `fg_companion.api.get_events`, `fg_companion.api.get_event`, etc.\n2. **Courses** (LMS) - uses `lms.api.get_courses`, etc.\n\n\n3. **DMs** (Raven) - uses Raven's API\n\nBut looking at `useRealApi()`, it checks `window.location.pathname.startsWith(\"/app\")` - which means at `/portal/*` it's false, so the mock is always used. The user probably wants the production flag to work differently for the portal, maybe checking for a different path or allowing the real APIs to be used even from the portal.\n\nLet me reconsider what's actually needed here. The task is to wire up the real API calls for Courses, DMs, and Events, which means I need to make the functions actually fetch from the backend instead of relying on mock data. I should check the `api.ts` file to understand how the API layer is structured and what methods are available.",
