    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a good understanding of the API layer. The `api.resource.call()` is used to call Frappe RPC methods (like `fg_companion.api.get_events`). Let me now look at the `fg_companion/api.py` to see what endpoints are available.\n\nThe key things to wire up in `store.ts`:\n1. **Events**: `getEvents()`, `getEvent()`, `getAttendees()` - should call `fg_companion.api.get_events`, `fg_companion.api.get_event`, etc.\n2. **DMs**: `getDMThreadsForUser()`, `getDMMessages()`, `openOrCreateDMWith()`, `sendDM()` - should call Raven's API\n\n\n3. **Courses**: `getCourses()`, `getChaptersForCourse()`, `getLessonsForChapter()`, etc. - should call LMS API\n\nLooking at the current `store.ts` implementation, I can see that `getDiscussionsAsync()` and `createDiscussion()` are already properly wired to use the real API when `useRealApi()` returns true, so those are working correctly. The main gap is getting the events and DMs endpoints properly connected.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider how `useRealApi()` works. It checks if we're in production and have a CSRF token, but on the portal at `/portal/`, the pathname doesn't start with `/app`, so it returns false and always uses the mock data instead. Since the backend is already seeded and the `fg_companion/api.py` endpoints are built out, the real issue is making sure the portal can actually access and use these real APIs.\n\nI should look at how gameplan structures its API calls to understand the right pattern, then wire up the key functions like `getEvents`, `getEvent`, and `getAttendees` to call the actual backend endpoints instead of relying on mock data.\n\nFor Raven's DM system, I need to figure out the correct API endpoints since that's a separate installed app. Let me start by examining gameplan's approach to see how they handle their API calls, then adapt that pattern for fg_companion's needs.\n\nNow I'm realizing the production check is backwards for the portal—it needs to use the real API when accessing `/portal/`, not mock data. I should adjust the condition to flip this logic so the portal consistently uses live data from the backend.",
      "timestamp": 1781985729146
