    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a good understanding. Let me now look at the `fg_companion/api.py` to see what endpoints we've defined there, and then wire up the store.ts properly.\n\nThe key Raven endpoints:\n- `raven_channel.get_all_channels` - GET DM channels for user\n- `raven_message.send_message` - POST to send a message\n- `raven_channel.create_direct_message_channel` - POST to create a DM\n\nFor Raven, channels have:\n- `name`: channel ID\n- `channel_name`: display name\n- `type`: \"Direct\" for DMs\n- `is_direct_message`: true for DMs\n\n\n- `peer_user_id`: the other user's ID in a DM\n\nNow I need to check the fg_companion/api.py file to see what's already been defined there.",
