    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "So LMS uses `frappe.call` for its API. The `get_courses` is a server-side function that can be called via `frappe.call('lms.utils.get_courses')`. \n\nFor the store.ts, the best approach is to use `api.resource.get('LMS Course')` to get courses via the standard Frappe resource API, since that's what the `fetchList` function uses.\n\nNow let me write the updated store.ts. I'll need to:\n\n1. Fix `IS_PRODUCTION` - change to check for CSRF token instead of pathname\n2. Add wire functions for:\n   - Events: `fg_companion.api.get_events`\n   - DMs: `raven_channel.get_all_channels` + `raven_message.send_message`\n   - Courses: `LMS Course` via `api.resource.get()`\n3. Add Raven message types to match what the frontend expects\n\nI'm going to write a comprehensive updated store.ts that brings all these pieces together, and I should also check what types need to be imported from the mock data to ensure the Raven DM types align properly with what the frontend is already using.\n\nWriting the updated store...",
      "timestamp": 1781985851455
