      "text": "\nHere's where we landed:\n\n**Done today:**\n- **DocTypes fixed** — moved from `fg_companion/doctype/` to the correct `fg_companion/fg_companion/doctype/` inner module path, then ran `bench migrate` to register them. The `module` field in `tabDocType` now correctly shows `FG Companion`.\n- **Database seeded** — 6 users, 2 GP Teams, 4 GP Projects, 5 GP Discussions, 2 FG Events (Welcome Week Mixer + CS Drop-in), and FG AI Settings all persisted in MariaDB.\n- **store.ts wired** — flipped the real-API gate from `startsWith('/app')` to simply checking for a CSRF cookie (present in both `/app/*` and `/portal/*` when logged in). Wire-up covers:\n  - **Events**: `fg_companion.api.get_events/get_event` + RSVP via `rsvp` RPC\n  - **Raven DMs**: `raven_channel.get_all_channels` → DM thread list, `raven_message.send_message` for sending, `create_direct_message_channel` for opening new threads\n  - **LMS Courses**: `api.resource.get('LMS Course')` with proper field selection\n- **Build clean** — `✓ built in 17.84s`, 80 modules, zero errors\n- **API smoke test green** — confirmed `fg_companion.api.get_events` returns both seeded events, discussions link to correct projects\n\nThe portal at `/portal/` will now hit the real Frappe APIs when logged in, falling back to mock data when not authenticated.",
